text: Adrijus Glebauskas (born 20 November 1994) is a Lithuanian high jumper. He finished fifth at the 2017 Summer Universiade,Final results and won the bronze medal at the 2019 Summer Universiade. He also competed at the 2015 European U23 Championships, the 2018 European Championships and the 2019 European Indoor Championships without reaching the final. His personal best jump is 2.27 metres, achieved in June 2019 in Utena. He improved it with 2.28 m in Palanga, achieved in July 2019. ==References== Category:1994 births Category:Living people Category:Lithuanian male high jumpers Category:European Games competitors for Lithuania Category:Athletes (track and field) at the 2019 European Games Category:Medalists at the 2019 Summer Universiade Category:Universiade medalists in athletics (track and field) Category:Universiade bronze medalists for Lithuania
